 for bestpractices and # Login / Signup Page

## Overview
Build a unified, production-ready authentication system for Archject that includes a combined Login / Signup page with SSO (OAuth), email/password flows, optional Two-Factor Authentication (SMS and authenticator app), email verification, a password reset flow, and connected Landing and Email Verification pages. Provide frontend UI following the project's design system and robust backend APIs, database models, and security best practices. Deliverables must be developer-ready: React/Vue components, REST API specifications, data models, integration notes for OAuth/2FA/email providers, and acceptance tests.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
This feature implements the Authentication surface for Archject studio users. The primary visual entry is a single, responsive Login / Signup page that lets users sign in, create an account, or authenticate via SSO providers (Google, Apple, Microsoft). The page links to a Password Reset flow and shows branding and privacy/terms notice. Signups require email verification before enabling critical actions. Optional Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) is available for users and can be enforced per-organization (enterprise customers) or per-user. The system must support SMS (via a provider) and authenticator apps (TOTP) as second factors.

Goals:
- Single unified entry point for authentication (Login & Signup toggle).
- Support OAuth SSO (Google, Apple, Microsoft) and standard email/password.
- Send email verification after signup and block sensitive actions until verified.
- Provide password reset via tokenized email links.
- Provide optional 2FA: TOTP (authenticator apps) and SMS-based codes.
- Provide small Landing and Email Verification pages as connection points for marketing and confirmation.
- Ensure accessibility, responsive layout, and strict security controls (rate-limiting, brute-force protection, hashed passwords, secured tokens, CSRF protection where applicable).

Connected features:
- 2FA enable/disable flows, recovery codes, and enterprise enforcement.
- Email verification tokens and flows that redirect to the Email Verification Page.
- Password reset request and set-password via secure token link.
- OAuth providers for SSO with ability to link new/existing accounts.

UI elements and visual guidance:
- Card-centered auth panel on #F7F7F9 backdrop. Card background #FFFFFF with subtle shadow and 8–12px radius.
- Header with Archject logo (or configured studio logo preview).
- Toggle: "Sign in" / "Create account" switch (inline, minimal).
- Primary form fields: Email (required), Password (required for email flow), Confirm Password (signup), Name / Studio name (signup optional), Show/Hide password icon, "Remember me" checkbox (login only).
- SSO buttons: three horizontally-stacked buttons (Google, Apple, Microsoft) styled as ghost buttons with provider icons and accent hover states. Use #0052CC for primary actions.
- Two-Factor steps: modal or card step UI when 2FA required, with TOTP QR + secret for setup, one-time recovery codes list, SMS input if SMS enabled, and "Use backup code" option.
- Links: "Forgot password?" -> Password Reset Page; "Resend verification email" on signup confirmation; Privacy & Terms text small under forms.
- Inline validation messages in #EF4444, success badges in #10B981.
- Micro-interactions: subtle elevation on card hover, focus ring on inputs (accent color).

API integrations:
- OAuth providers: Google, Apple, Microsoft via OAuth 2.0 / OpenID Connect. Backend must implement provider configuration, callback endpoints, and account linking.
- Email delivery: transactional email service (SendGrid/Postmark/Mailgun) for verification and password reset.
- SMS provider: Twilio or configurable SMS provider for SMS 2FA.
- Optional: Integrate an authenticator app flow using TOTP (RFC 6238) and store secrets securely.

## Components to Build
- Frontend Pages/Components:
  - UnifiedAuthCard (Login/Signup toggle)
  - EmailPasswordForm (fields + validation + show/hide password)
  - SSOButtons (Google, Apple, Microsoft)
  - TwoFactorModal (setup and verify flows)
  - PasswordResetRequestPage
  - PasswordResetSetPage (tokenized link)
  - EmailVerificationLandingPage (confirmation status)
  - Landing Page (hero, features, pricing CTA linking to signup or demo)
  - Small reusable components: Input, Button, Checkbox, LinkText, Toast/Alert, LoadingSpinner, QRCodeDisplay, RecoveryCodesList
- Backend:
  - Auth API: register, login, oauth callbacks, linkAccount, logout, refresh token, verifyEmail, resendVerification, requestPasswordReset, resetPassword, enable2FA, verify2FA, disable2FA, generateRecoveryCodes.
  - DB models: Users, AuthProviders (OAuth links), Sessions (refresh tokens), EmailTokens, PasswordResetTokens, 2FASecrets, RecoveryCodes, Audit logs (login attempts, 2FA events).
  - Background jobs: sendEmail, sendSMS, token cleanup jobs.
- DevOps / Config:
  - Environment config for OAuth client IDs/secrets, email/SMS providers, JWT signing keys, rate-limit configuration.
  - CI tests for API endpoints and E2E auth flows.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
Stack: React (with TypeScript) or Vue 3 (TS), using router and state management (Redux/RTK Query or Pinia/Axios). CSS: Tailwind-compatible utility classes or styled-components; use provided design tokens/colors/spacing.

Pages & Components:
- UnifiedAuthPage
  - Layout: centered card (max-width 420px), left side blank/illustration on desktop; mobile full-width.
  - Toggle: two segmented buttons: "Sign in" & "Create account" with animated underline.
  - Email/password form with client-side validation:
    - Email (type=email), Password (type=password, show/hide toggle), Confirm password (signup), Name/Studio optional.
    - Password strength meter for signup (min 12 chars recommended or per policy).
    - Submit button primary (#0052CC) and disabled while submitting.
  - SSOButtons: show all providers; clicking opens OAuth popup/redirect to backend /auth/oauth/:provider endpoint.
  - Forgot password link under login fields.
  - Inline error/success messages, toast notifications.
  - Acceptable Accessibility: aria-labels, role attributes on modals, keyboard focus management.
- TwoFactorModal / 2FA Setup:
  - For TOTP setup: show QR code (QR library) with manual secret copy, "Verify" input to accept a TOTP code.
  - For SMS: phone number input, send code button, verify code input.
  - Show recovery codes after successful setup with download/copy button.
  - Option UI to "Remember this device" for 30 days using secure cookie + device ID.
- Password Reset Pages:
  - Request page: email input, "Send reset link" button, success state with instruction.
  - Set new password page: validate token from URL, show new password and confirm fields, submit to backend to set password.
- Email Verification Page:
  - Page that verifies token in URL via API and displays success or failure messages, with CTA button to go to Dashboard or login.
- Landing Page:
  - Marketing hero, feature list, pricing CTA, "Sign up" and "Request a demo" buttons linking to auth/signup or demo request.
- UX Requirements:
  - Graceful handling of OAuth errors, token expirations, and email verification pending states.
  - Loading and disabled states for network operations.
  - Use the typography and spacing guidelines; components must reuse tokens.

### Backend
Stack: Node.js (TypeScript) with Express/NestJS, or other language/framework per project (provide REST endpoints). Use PostgreSQL (or other relational DB) + Redis for ephemeral state (rate-limiting, session store). JWT access/refresh tokens, with refresh tokens stored hashed in DB.

APIs to implement (details below in Technical Specifications):
- POST /api/auth/register
- POST /api/auth/login
- POST /api/auth/oauth/:provider (initiate) and GET /api/auth/oauth/:provider/callback
- POST /api/auth/verify-email
- POST /api/auth/resend-verification
- POST /api/auth/password-reset/request
- POST /api/auth/password-reset/confirm
- POST /api/auth/2fa/setup
- POST /api/auth/2fa/verify
- POST /api/auth/2fa/sms/send
- POST /api/auth/2fa/sms/verify
- POST /api/auth/logout
- POST /api/auth/token/refresh

Core backend requirements:
- Passwords hashed with Argon2 or bcrypt (bcrypt cost >= 12).
- Use prepared statements / ORM (Prisma/TypeORM/Sequelize) to avoid injection.
- Email tokens & password reset tokens: cryptographically random, single-use, time-limited (e.g., 24h for verification, 1h for reset).
- TOTP according to RFC 6238; store TOTP secret encrypted at rest (use KMS or app-level encryption).
- Recovery codes: generate 8 codes, single-use, stored hashed.
- Rate-limiting and IP-based throttling for login, password-reset, 2FA attempts.
- Audit trail for security events (logins, failed logins, password resets, 2FA events).
- CSRF protections for cookie-based auth flows.
- Session invalidation on password change or logout: revoke refresh tokens.

### Integration
- OAuth: backend handles OAuth flow, matches provider identity to user by email. If user exists and provider not linked, prompt to link account (if logged in) or sign in. Implement account linking endpoint.
- Email verification: after register, backend creates verification token and sends email with verification link to /email/verify?token=...; link opens Email Verification Page which calls verify endpoint and then redirects.
- Password reset: request endpoint sends email with secure token link to password reset page with token param.
- 2FA flows:
  - Signup/login: if user has 2FA configured, require 2FA verification after password success before issuing access token.
  - Setup: allow enabling 2FA from account settings; for enterprise enforcement, block actions until enabled.
- Frontend/Backend contract: all endpoints return consistent JSON payloads with errors { code, message, fields? } and success { data }.

## User Experience Flow
1. Visitor arrives at Landing Page; clicks "Sign up" or "Log in" -> navigates to Unified Auth Page.
2. On Unified Auth Page:
   - New user toggles to "Create account", fills email/password and optional name/studio, clicks "Create account".
   - Backend creates user with email_verified=false, sends verification email, and returns success; frontend shows "Check your email" state with "Resend" option.
   - If user chooses SSO (Google/Apple/Microsoft): click triggers OAuth redirect. Backend processes callback, if first-time sign-up sends email verification OR (preferred) uses provider's verified_email claim to mark verified. If email matches existing account, prompt to link or sign in.
3. After successful registration/login:
   - If the account requires 2FA, user is redirected to 2FA verification step. On initial setup, show QR code and backup codes flow.
   - On successful 2FA (or if not enabled), issue JWT access token and refresh token, set secure cookie (httpOnly, secure, SameSite=strict/none depending on needs) and redirect to Dashboard.
4. Email verification:
   - Clicking verification link lands on Email Verification Page. It calls verify endpoint, shows success or error, and provides CTA to login or go to Dashboard depending on session state.
5. Password reset:
   - User clicks "Forgot password?" -> Password Reset Request Page, enters email. Backend sends reset token email.
   - Clicking link opens Password Reset Set Page where user sets new password. On success invalidate all refresh tokens and log event.
6. Account Security:
   - Users can enable/disable 2FA in account settings (this is a related feature but must be supported by backend endpoints and initial flows).
   - Recovery codes provided during 2FA setup must be downloadable and shown once.

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models (Postgres example):

Users
- id: uuid (PK)
- email: varchar, unique, indexed, not null
- email_verified: boolean, default false
- name: varchar
- studio_name: varchar (nullable)
- password_hash: varchar (nullable for SSO-only accounts)
- created_at: timestamptz
- updated_at: timestamptz
- is_active: boolean (soft-deactivate)
- is_enterprise_enforced_2fa: boolean (organization-level enforcement or via Org table)

AuthProviders
- id: uuid
- user_id: uuid (FK -> Users)
- provider: enum('google','apple','microsoft', ...)
- provider_user_id: varchar
- provider_metadata: jsonb
- created_at

Sessions / RefreshTokens
- id: uuid
- user_id: uuid
- refresh_token_hash: varchar
- device_info: jsonb
- expires_at: timestamptz
- created_at

EmailTokens (verification)
- id: uuid
- user_id: uuid
- token_hash: varchar
- type: enum('email_verification','password_reset')
- expires_at: timestamptz
- used: boolean
- created_at

TwoFASecrets
- id: uuid
- user_id: uuid
- totp_secret_encrypted: varchar
- sms_phone_number: varchar (nullable)
- enabled_totp: boolean
- enabled_sms: boolean
- created_at

RecoveryCodes
- id: uuid
- user_id: uuid
- code_hash: varchar
- used: boolean
- created_at

AuditLogs
- id: uuid
- user_id: uuid (nullable)
- event_type: enum('login_success','login_failure','password_reset','2fa_success','2fa_failure','email_sent','oauth_linked',...)
- ip_address: inet
- user_agent: text
- metadata: jsonb
- created_at

- API Endpoints (REST)
1. POST /api/auth/register
   - Body: { email, password, name?, studio_name? }
   - Response: 201 { message, next: 'verify_email' }
   - Creates user, sends verification email.

2. POST /api/auth/login
   - Body: { email, password, rememberMe? }
   - Response: 200 { requires2FA: boolean, temp_session_id? } or { accessToken, refreshToken }
   - On requires2FA true, return a short-lived temp token indicating password was correct and user must verify 2FA.

3. POST /api/auth/oauth/:provider/start
   - Response: Redirect URL or 302 to provider.

4. GET /api/auth/oauth/:provider/callback
   - Exchange code for token, find/create user, set email verification based on provider claims, issue tokens or require 2FA.

5. POST /api/auth/verify-email
   - Body: { token }
   - Response: 200 { success }

6. POST /api/auth/resend-verification
   - Body: { email }
   - Response: 200 { success }

7. POST /api/auth/password-reset/request
   - Body: { email }
   - Response: 200 { message } (always return generic message to avoid email enumeration)

8. POST /api/auth/password-reset/confirm
   - Body: { token, newPassword }
   - Response: 200 { success }

9. POST /api/auth/2fa/setup (authenticated)
   - Body: { type: 'totp'|'sms', phone? }
   - Response: 200 { qr: dataURI, secret: plainTextSecret (only once) } (secret must be ephemeral on the response)

10. POST /api/auth/2fa/verify
    - Body: { type, code, temp_session_id? }
    - Response: 200 { accessToken, refreshToken } or success for enablement.

11. POST /api/auth/2fa/sms/send
    - Body: { phone, temp_session_id? }
    - Response: 200 { success }

12. POST /api/auth/logout
    - Body: { refreshToken? }
    - Response: 200 { success } (invalidate refresh token)

13. POST /api/auth/token/refresh
    - Body: { refreshToken }
    - Response: 200 { accessToken, refreshToken }

- Security
  - Password hashing: Argon2id or bcrypt (bcrypt rounds >= 12).
  - Tokens: access token TTL short (e.g., 15 min), refresh tokens longer (7–30 days), refresh tokens stored hashed.
  - Token creation: use secure random bytes, not predictable.
  - TOTP: secrets stored encrypted with application key or KMS; verification uses standard TOTP library; allow clock skew tolerance +/-1 step.
  - Password policy: minimum length 12, require at least 1 uppercase, 1 lowercase, 1 digit, and 1 symbol (configurable).
  - Rate limiting: per-IP and per-account limits for login attempts, password-reset requests, token verify endpoints.
  - Brute-force prevention: exponential backoff account lockout after configurable failed attempts; provide unlock via password reset, admin override, or timed reset.
  - CSRF protection: for cookie-based flows; otherwise require tokens in Authorization header.
  - XSS: escape all user-provided text; no secrets in URLs (except token in one-time verification flows is acceptable but minimize exposure).
  - Secure cookies: httpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Strict/None depending on domain requirements.

- Validation
  - Email: RFC 5322 compliant, normalized to lowercase, domain validation optional.
  - Password: enforce password policy above; disallow common weak passwords via list or zxcvbn check.
  - Phone number: E.164 format (use libphonenumber).
  - OAuth callbacks: validate state parameter to prevent CSRF during OAuth.
  - Token usage: single-use tokens for email verification & password reset; mark used and delete after consumption.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] UnifiedAuthPage displays Login and Signup toggle and validates inputs on client-side with accessible markup.
- [ ] SSO buttons initiate OAuth flow and backend can handle provider callbacks to create/login users (mockable during integration).
- [ ] Registration creates user record with email_verified=false and sends verification email with single-use token.
- [ ] Clicking Email Verification link verifies token, updates email_verified=true, displays Email Verification Page, and redirects appropriately.
- [ ] Login flow supports email/password and will require 2FA if the user has it enabled; issuing tokens only after successful 2FA.
- [ ] Password reset request sends email with secure time-limited token; token allows setting new password and invalidates previous sessions.
- [ ] 2FA setup for TOTP displays QR and secret once, verifies one-time code, generates recovery codes, and enforces verification on subsequent logins.
- [ ] Backend stores all secrets/tokens encrypted/hashed and logs critical security events in AuditLogs.
- [ ] All endpoints handle error conditions gracefully, rate-limited, and return consistent JSON error objects.
- [ ] Landing Page, Password Reset pages, and Email Verification Page match visual style, are responsive, and accessible.

## UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system and visual style exactly as specified.

- Layout & typography: use Inter or equivalent; H1 ~28px, body 15–16px; 12-column grid; large whitespace as described.
- Colors and components: use the exact hex palette provided. Primary CTAs use #0052CC; errors use #EF4444; success uses #10B981.
- Card design: centered white card with subtle shadow, 8–12px radius.
- Buttons: primary solid #0052CC with white text; secondary ghost buttons for SSO and less prominent actions.
- Inputs: rounded edges, border #D1D5DB, focus ring in accent color or subtle shadow. Show inline validation errors in #EF4444.
- Micro-interactions: smooth transitions, hover elevation for cards and buttons, show loading spinner inside buttons on submit.
- Accessibility: ensure color contrast, keyboard navigation, aria attributes for form controls and modal dialog for 2FA setup.

### Visual specifics for components
- UnifiedAuthCard max-width: 420px; vertical padding 28–32px; horizontal padding 24px.
- Toggle segmented control: background #F3F4F6, active segment with #FFFFFF and accent underline 2px #0052CC.
- SSO buttons: white background, light border #E5E7EB, provider icon left (24px), text #111827, hover background #F3F4F6.
- Verification and Reset pages: simple cards with an icon, headline H2 ~22px, body text 15–16px, primary CTA button to proceed.

## Implementation Notes & Developer Hints
- Use environment variables for provider secrets and keys. Provide dev-mode stubs or instructions for local testing (e.g., OAuth test credentials, local SMTP Sen[email] or Mailtrap).
- Write automated tests: unit tests for auth logic, integration tests for endpoints, and E2E tests for happy-path signup/login/2FA flows (use Cypress/Playwright).
- Provide Postman/Insomnia collection or OpenAPI spec for all auth endpoints.
- Document data retention and security policies for tokens and audit logs.
- Design APIs to return opaque errors to clients and avoid leaking whether an email exists during reset/resend endpoints.
- Provide UI copy variants for messages (success, error, pending verification) and microcopy for 2FA setup & recovery codes.

## Deliverables
- Frontend code: pages and components described (React+TS or Vue+TS), ready to integrate into Archject frontend.
- Backend code: auth service with endpoints, DB migrations/schema, and secrets management notes.
- Configuration & Deployment README: env vars, third-party provider setup, local dev instructions.
- OpenAPI/Swagger documentation and Postman collection.
- Test suite: unit tests and E2E test scenarios covering Acceptance Criteria.
- Design assets: Figma or style tokens mapping for colors, typography, spacing, and component states.

Implement this feature with security, reliability, and the provided visual system in mind. Prioritize clear developer documentation and testability so the authentication system can be audited and extended (SAML/SCIM, enterprise provisioning) in the future. for style.

CRITICAL DESIGN REQUIREMENTS:
- You MUST follow ALL design principles and patterns specified in the Design Reference above
- Do NOT deviate from the design specifications without explicit user permission
- Implement ALL visual design elements (colors, typography, spacing, shadows, animations) as specified
- Follow the layout patterns and component designs exactly as documented
- Ensure all interactions and micro-animations match the reference specifications

CRITICAL TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS:
- React 18.3.1, React Router 6.30.1
- Tailwind CSS v3 with tailwind.config.js and custom keyframes
- @tailwindcss/typography plugin for rich text content
- Tailwind CSS animations (NOT Motion library or framer-motion)
- Sonner for toasts
- Recharts for data visualization
- Native fetch() with API utilities in src/lib/api.ts
- Design system with CSS custom properties
- Use RGB color values for theming
- When Supabase is configured: use Edge Functions for LLM and server-only logic; never expose API keys in the client

=== TASK ===
# Login / Signup Page

## Overview
Build a unified, production-ready authentication system for Archject that includes a combined Login / Signup page with SSO (OAuth), email/password flows, optional Two-Factor Authentication (SMS and authenticator app), email verification, a password reset flow, and connected Landing and Email Verification pages. Provide frontend UI following the project's design system and robust backend APIs, database models, and security best practices. Deliverables must be developer-ready: React/Vue components, REST API specifications, data models, integration notes for OAuth/2FA/email providers, and acceptance tests.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
This feature implements the Authentication surface for Archject studio users. The primary visual entry is a single, responsive Login / Signup page that lets users sign in, create an account, or authenticate via SSO providers (Google, Apple, Microsoft). The page links to a Password Reset flow and shows branding and privacy/terms notice. Signups require email verification before enabling critical actions. Optional Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) is available for users and can be enforced per-organization (enterprise customers) or per-user. The system must support SMS (via a provider) and authenticator apps (TOTP) as second factors.

Goals:
- Single unified entry point for authentication (Login & Signup toggle).
- Support OAuth SSO (Google, Apple, Microsoft) and standard email/password.
- Send email verification after signup and block sensitive actions until verified.
- Provide password reset via tokenized email links.
- Provide optional 2FA: TOTP (authenticator apps) and SMS-based codes.
- Provide small Landing and Email Verification pages as connection points for marketing and confirmation.
- Ensure accessibility, responsive layout, and strict security controls (rate-limiting, brute-force protection, hashed passwords, secured tokens, CSRF protection where applicable).

Connected features:
- 2FA enable/disable flows, recovery codes, and enterprise enforcement.
- Email verification tokens and flows that redirect to the Email Verification Page.
- Password reset request and set-password via secure token link.
- OAuth providers for SSO with ability to link new/existing accounts.

UI elements and visual guidance:
- Card-centered auth panel on #F7F7F9 backdrop. Card background #FFFFFF with subtle shadow and 8–12px radius.
- Header with Archject logo (or configured studio logo preview).
- Toggle: "Sign in" / "Create account" switch (inline, minimal).
- Primary form fields: Email (required), Password (required for email flow), Confirm Password (signup), Name / Studio name (signup optional), Show/Hide password icon, "Remember me" checkbox (login only).
- SSO buttons: three horizontally-stacked buttons (Google, Apple, Microsoft) styled as ghost buttons with provider icons and accent hover states. Use #0052CC for primary actions.
- Two-Factor steps: modal or card step UI when 2FA required, with TOTP QR + secret for setup, one-time recovery codes list, SMS input if SMS enabled, and "Use backup code" option.
- Links: "Forgot password?" -> Password Reset Page; "Resend verification email" on signup confirmation; Privacy & Terms text small under forms.
- Inline validation messages in #EF4444, success badges in #10B981.
- Micro-interactions: subtle elevation on card hover, focus ring on inputs (accent color).

API integrations:
- OAuth providers: Google, Apple, Microsoft via OAuth 2.0 / OpenID Connect. Backend must implement provider configuration, callback endpoints, and account linking.
- Email delivery: transactional email service (SendGrid/Postmark/Mailgun) for verification and password reset.
- SMS provider: Twilio or configurable SMS provider for SMS 2FA.
- Optional: Integrate an authenticator app flow using TOTP (RFC 6238) and store secrets securely.

## Components to Build
- Frontend Pages/Components:
  - UnifiedAuthCard (Login/Signup toggle)
  - EmailPasswordForm (fields + validation + show/hide password)
  - SSOButtons (Google, Apple, Microsoft)
  - TwoFactorModal (setup and verify flows)
  - PasswordResetRequestPage
  - PasswordResetSetPage (tokenized link)
  - EmailVerificationLandingPage (confirmation status)
  - Landing Page (hero, features, pricing CTA linking to signup or demo)
  - Small reusable components: Input, Button, Checkbox, LinkText, Toast/Alert, LoadingSpinner, QRCodeDisplay, RecoveryCodesList
- Backend:
  - Auth API: register, login, oauth callbacks, linkAccount, logout, refresh token, verifyEmail, resendVerification, requestPasswordReset, resetPassword, enable2FA, verify2FA, disable2FA, generateRecoveryCodes.
  - DB models: Users, AuthProviders (OAuth links), Sessions (refresh tokens), EmailTokens, PasswordResetTokens, 2FASecrets, RecoveryCodes, Audit logs (login attempts, 2FA events).
  - Background jobs: sendEmail, sendSMS, token cleanup jobs.
- DevOps / Config:
  - Environment config for OAuth client IDs/secrets, email/SMS providers, JWT signing keys, rate-limit configuration.
  - CI tests for API endpoints and E2E auth flows.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
Stack: React (with TypeScript) or Vue 3 (TS), using router and state management (Redux/RTK Query or Pinia/Axios). CSS: Tailwind-compatible utility classes or styled-components; use provided design tokens/colors/spacing.

Pages & Components:
- UnifiedAuthPage
  - Layout: centered card (max-width 420px), left side blank/illustration on desktop; mobile full-width.
  - Toggle: two segmented buttons: "Sign in" & "Create account" with animated underline.
  - Email/password form with client-side validation:
    - Email (type=email), Password (type=password, show/hide toggle), Confirm password (signup), Name/Studio optional.
    - Password strength meter for signup (min 12 chars recommended or per policy).
    - Submit button primary (#0052CC) and disabled while submitting.
  - SSOButtons: show all providers; clicking opens OAuth popup/redirect to backend /auth/oauth/:provider endpoint.
  - Forgot password link under login fields.
  - Inline error/success messages, toast notifications.
  - Acceptable Accessibility: aria-labels, role attributes on modals, keyboard focus management.
- TwoFactorModal / 2FA Setup:
  - For TOTP setup: show QR code (QR library) with manual secret copy, "Verify" input to accept a TOTP code.
  - For SMS: phone number input, send code button, verify code input.
  - Show recovery codes after successful setup with download/copy button.
  - Option UI to "Remember this device" for 30 days using secure cookie + device ID.
- Password Reset Pages:
  - Request page: email input, "Send reset link" button, success state with instruction.
  - Set new password page: validate token from URL, show new password and confirm fields, submit to backend to set password.
- Email Verification Page:
  - Page that verifies token in URL via API and displays success or failure messages, with CTA button to go to Dashboard or login.
- Landing Page:
  - Marketing hero, feature list, pricing CTA, "Sign up" and "Request a demo" buttons linking to auth/signup or demo request.
- UX Requirements:
  - Graceful handling of OAuth errors, token expirations, and email verification pending states.
  - Loading and disabled states for network operations.
  - Use the typography and spacing guidelines; components must reuse tokens.

### Backend
Stack: Node.js (TypeScript) with Express/NestJS, or other language/framework per project (provide REST endpoints). Use PostgreSQL (or other relational DB) + Redis for ephemeral state (rate-limiting, session store). JWT access/refresh tokens, with refresh tokens stored hashed in DB.

APIs to implement (details below in Technical Specifications):
- POST /api/auth/register
- POST /api/auth/login
- POST /api/auth/oauth/:provider (initiate) and GET /api/auth/oauth/:provider/callback
- POST /api/auth/verify-email
- POST /api/auth/resend-verification
- POST /api/auth/password-reset/request
- POST /api/auth/password-reset/confirm
- POST /api/auth/2fa/setup
- POST /api/auth/2fa/verify
- POST /api/auth/2fa/sms/send
- POST /api/auth/2fa/sms/verify
- POST /api/auth/logout
- POST /api/auth/token/refresh

Core backend requirements:
- Passwords hashed with Argon2 or bcrypt (bcrypt cost >= 12).
- Use prepared statements / ORM (Prisma/TypeORM/Sequelize) to avoid injection.
- Email tokens & password reset tokens: cryptographically random, single-use, time-limited (e.g., 24h for verification, 1h for reset).
- TOTP according to RFC 6238; store TOTP secret encrypted at rest (use KMS or app-level encryption).
- Recovery codes: generate 8 codes, single-use, stored hashed.
- Rate-limiting and IP-based throttling for login, password-reset, 2FA attempts.
- Audit trail for security events (logins, failed logins, password resets, 2FA events).
- CSRF protections for cookie-based auth flows.
- Session invalidation on password change or logout: revoke refresh tokens.

### Integration
- OAuth: backend handles OAuth flow, matches provider identity to user by email. If user exists and provider not linked, prompt to link account (if logged in) or sign in. Implement account linking endpoint.
- Email verification: after register, backend creates verification token and sends email with verification link to /email/verify?token=...; link opens Email Verification Page which calls verify endpoint and then redirects.
- Password reset: request endpoint sends email with secure token link to password reset page with token param.
- 2FA flows:
  - Signup/login: if user has 2FA configured, require 2FA verification after password success before issuing access token.
  - Setup: allow enabling 2FA from account settings; for enterprise enforcement, block actions until enabled.
- Frontend/Backend contract: all endpoints return consistent JSON payloads with errors { code, message, fields? } and success { data }.

## User Experience Flow
1. Visitor arrives at Landing Page; clicks "Sign up" or "Log in" -> navigates to Unified Auth Page.
2. On Unified Auth Page:
   - New user toggles to "Create account", fills email/password and optional name/studio, clicks "Create account".
   - Backend creates user with email_verified=false, sends verification email, and returns success; frontend shows "Check your email" state with "Resend" option.
   - If user chooses SSO (Google/Apple/Microsoft): click triggers OAuth redirect. Backend processes callback, if first-time sign-up sends email verification OR (preferred) uses provider's verified_email claim to mark verified. If email matches existing account, prompt to link or sign in.
3. After successful registration/login:
   - If the account requires 2FA, user is redirected to 2FA verification step. On initial setup, show QR code and backup codes flow.
   - On successful 2FA (or if not enabled), issue JWT access token and refresh token, set secure cookie (httpOnly, secure, SameSite=strict/none depending on needs) and redirect to Dashboard.
4. Email verification:
   - Clicking verification link lands on Email Verification Page. It calls verify endpoint, shows success or error, and provides CTA to login or go to Dashboard depending on session state.
5. Password reset:
   - User clicks "Forgot password?" -> Password Reset Request Page, enters email. Backend sends reset token email.
   - Clicking link opens Password Reset Set Page where user sets new password. On success invalidate all refresh tokens and log event.
6. Account Security:
   - Users can enable/disable 2FA in account settings (this is a related feature but must be supported by backend endpoints and initial flows).
   - Recovery codes provided during 2FA setup must be downloadable and shown once.

